    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira is a medium-sized woman, regal in bearing. She scrutinizes you with a look that manages to convey both admiration and disdain.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>[OLD NODE; SHOULD NOT PLAY; DELETE AFTER REVISIONS ARE FINAL]

The Memovira stands before you, her gaze strong and unflinching, though her face is lined and stress marks her mouth. "You have retrieved the second Merecaster, I assume. I will need to examine it to ensure that this is the same one entrusted to my care."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[OLD NODE; SHOULD NOT PLAY; DELETE AFTER REVISIONS ARE FINAL]

The Memovira's face is red with anger, and you can see the veins throbbing in her forehead. Her voice has lost its cultured edge. "You're five seconds away from feeding the laaks, usurper. Explain your actions or die."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can't we negotiate?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Negotiate? You've stripped the Bloom from me, and you want to negotiate? Negotiate with *this*." She signals, and her thugs attack!</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I didn't get where I am today through *trust*. Let me see it. Pretend it's the key to my vault, because in a very real sense it is."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>She takes it from you. "Then we have a deal. Never let it be said that I renege on my bargains."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your instincts were correct - she *is* afraid of you. She hesitates a moment, and something in the cast of your face convinces her. "Very well." She passes you the shunt and gives you a key to the the Merecaster's vault. "I tell you now, though: I have no idea how to reverse the shunt's effects. Search my mind if you wish, Satsada - I find it a delicious irony, but my malice does not extend that far."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank 9</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>It seems she's gotten her hands on a holographic projector. Though if so, the image is much more solid than one would expect.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>

No, she *is* there, at least partially. She's using some kind of phased teleporter, allowing her to appear without exposing herself to dangerous elements.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Some strange magic allows her to be in two places at once.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her eyes cut to Riastrad and Matkina. A slight tightening around her eyes suggests that their presence isn't entirely welcome.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>

Her eyes cut to Matkina. A slight tightening around her eyes suggests a wariness toward Matkina.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>

Her eyes cut to Riastrad. A slight tightening around her eyes suggests that Riastrad shares some history with the Memovira.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>Though her words are cultured, her voice is rough - perhaps an artifact of low upbringing. "Dracogen was... effusive in his praise for your skills. I've been following your movements myself. You moved the Trade Post out of the depths? There are very, very few people who could manage such a feat."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her eyes are piercing as they sweep across you. "I've dealt with castoffs before, of course. I've found your kind to be tenacious, resourceful, and skilled. And I *know* the one you are looking for. I can tell you where she is hiding."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You mean you thought you could milk the connection for all it was worth."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hush, Matkina."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well said, Matkina. But I want to hear what she has to say."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My apologies, Memovira. I wish to hear what you have to say."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira ignores the interruption and continues.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The First is powerful. If you tell me where she is, I'm sure together we can rescue Ishen more easily."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I had a few questions, actually..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll be back from the Bloom's heart shortly, then. Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The First *is* alive then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I am grateful for any help you can provide."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you want in return?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I do apologize if I gave the impression that this was a discussion." Her voice hardens. "I have made my offer. Rescue my friend from the Bloom's heart and you shall have the location of your precious First. Fail, and you will not. Do I make myself clear?" Her voice returns to its ordinary tones. "Now, if you'll excuse me, I have an organization to maintain."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>::fwwwipp::

{SCRIPT: Need to make the Memovira disappear using the teleport/transdimensional VFX here. -JF}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>::fwwwipp::</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have learned something about the Bloom, and it is crucial to your survival that you hear me out. The Bloom has already turned against you, and it will devour you if you don't flee now."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're already dead, Memovira."  Attack her!</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>The way she looks at you and holds herself suggests that she might be wary... or even slightly afraid?... of said accomplishment.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>Hand it over.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I had a few questions first."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You can trust me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As I mentioned earlier, I am extraordinarily busy. If you want questions answered, speak to a guide like Grisseler. Give me the Merecaster so that I can see it for myself."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>She takes it in her hands and looks it over carefully. Satisfied, she returns it to you. "Follow me."

{SCRIPT: She paths to the Vault door, unlocks it with some sort of biometric device, and continues with her speech when the PC joins her in the Vault. When the party joins her, the Vault door closes}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have lost more men than I care to think about while trying to recover him. As a castoff, however, you have certain... advantages my minions do not."

Her tone becomes curt. "With the recent fluctuations in the Bloom's layout, I no longer know the path to reach the Heart. I suggest you talk to someone who knows the Bloom well, if you cannot discover the way yourself."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>Satsada's voice emerges from Riastrad's mouth: "I see you have the shunt that you used to separate me from my love. I want you to use it to bring me back to the land of the flesh."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I thought about destroying you, you know. Now that you're here and all three Merecasters are present, that... *thing* that pursues you would probably be mollified and cease its assault if you were all dead. In fact, I still haven't made up my mind. I might be persuaded."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That wasn't part of our bargain, Satsada. Besides, I'd think you'd be delighted to be so... intimate... with your mate. You were a girl silly in love, and I lost good fighters trying to save you from your mistake. No, I don't think so."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>Riastrad begins to form a blade from his weapon. "I think I can convince you to change your mind."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>Attack the Memovira!

{SCRIPTER: Start Crisis/Tussle}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait a moment, Satsada. I think we can resolve this peacefully."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait, Riastrad. We could find a mutually agreable solution."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait. Let's think this through."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You want *us* to pay *you*?" Matkina looks around. "Odd. I don't think you have enough power here to protect you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What would it take to change your mind?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You know who we are. I know that you're scared of me. Do you really want to start a fight?"

{CRIT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What would it take to change your mind?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira laughs. "Did you really think I would leave myself unprotected near you, Matkina? I knew you were ignorant, but I didn't think you were stupid." She sighs overemphatically. "Oh well. Another illusion shattered."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>Attack the Memovira without another word.

{SCRIPT:  Start the crisis!}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
