      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your instincts were correct - she *is* afraid of you. She hesitates a moment, and something in the cast of your face convinces her. "Very well." She passes you the key to the vault containing the final Merecaster. "But leave. Leave now before whatever hunts you finds you here and dooms us all."

{DESIGN: Items are MemoviraMerecasterKey}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I am not so easily frightened. If it's a fight you want, you'll get it, but I'm sure we can find a better way."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I am not convinced. Lay out your case."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Would you like to know what I found in the Bloom's heart? Let me tell you..."

{CRIT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Actually, fighting would be easier." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>You speak long and eloquently, telling her of what you have seen in the Bloom and how it reacted to you. She listens. At last, she says: "You... you spoke to the Bloom? How was this information denied me? You..." 

She looks truly flustered for the first time since you have seen her, and then she gathers her composure. "You are certain that the Bloom will devour me?" Her eyes search your face for any hint of deception, and she finds none.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>You speak long and eloquently, telling her of what you have seen in the Bloom and how it reacted to you. She listens. She watches you, her eyes growing ever harder, and at last she holds up her hand. "Are you stalling for time? This may be one of the most foolish things I have ever heard. Guards: kill them all."

{SCRIPT: If c4401_GrisselerOnPlayersSide = 1, then Grisseler should join the battle on the player's side.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have uncovered evidence of the Bloom's history... not just yours, but the Memoviras before you."

{CRIT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have uncovered evidence of the Bloom's history... not just yours, but the Memoviras before you."

{CRIT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have uncovered evidence of the Bloom's history... not just yours, but the Memoviras before you."

{CRIT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>100</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I sincerely hope this means I get to kill you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>101</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Matkina, you have tried before and you've failed. This is because you. Are. A failure." The Memovira turns back to you. "Well? Convince me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>102</ID>
      <DefaultText>"M'lady, I hate to interrupt..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>She turns her furious gaze upon him. "Out with it, or you'll share his fate."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>She turns her furious gaze upon him. "Out with it, or you'll share her fate."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>105</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Bloom let this fella walk straight into the Heart. Didn't even put up a fight. You ever hear of that before?" He shrugs. "Might be too late to turn this around."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"The Bloom let this lady walk straight into the Heart. Didn't even put up a fight. You ever hear of that before?" He shrugs. "Might be too late to turn this around."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>107</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You know Walks-without-fear? He was the old Memovira. The Bloom devoured his spirit, and it will do the same to you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>108</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I spoke with the Observant Speck. She told me of the endless cycle of the Bloom's hunger, and what it does with its old rulers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>109</ID>
      <DefaultText>"His spirit was broken before I ever took power. I said *convince me.*"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>111</ID>
      <DefaultText>Though her words are cultured, her voice is rough, as if her voice had been trained to shout and growl orders for decades. "Dracogen has told me of your skills, and I have followed your movements with great interest. You seem to move through the Bloom with little trepidation. That's good... very good."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>112</ID>
      <DefaultText>She pretends to hide a contemptuous smirk. "Dracogen told you otherwise, didn't he? He knows far more than he lets on. He also knows better than to give away *my* bargaining chips. Your information is correct - the First is alive. But like Dracogen, I'm not inclined to giving away my secrets for free. I understand she's been hidden from your kind for over a century. I have no qualms about betraying her, but the cost will be steep."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>113</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've lost someone, an important member of my organization. You've no doubt heard of the recent changes in the Bloom - perhaps you have even heard the rumor that it has turned against *me*. To some extent that is true. Ishen is a victim of that betrayal."

She looks at the floor, saddened. "Ishen was my best scholar, a genius with the numenera. Through my own means, I've divined that he still lives, but I cannot reach him. The Bloom has taken Ishen to its Heart."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>114</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm sure you are." She sneers. "Unfortunately, I am not one to give my secrets away for free, especially not *this* secret. I understand that this First Castoff has been hidden from your kind for over a century. Rest assured, I have no qualms about betraying her, but the cost will be steep."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So untrusting. So wise." She chuckles. "I understand that this First Castoff has been hidden from your kind for over a century - that you thought she was dead! Well, know that I have no qualms about betraying her, but the cost will be steep."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>116</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Merecaster you received from Dracogen is a part of the key that will activate the third, the one I have stored in my vault. The one you will retrieve from the Bloom's heart is another part of the key. Taking the one I have stored safely away now serves no purpose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>117</ID>
      <DefaultText>She glares at him, her resistance crumbling slightly, and looks back to you. Her eyes narrow and she says, "What else? Have you anything else to tell me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>118</ID>
      <DefaultText>She scoffs,"That old crone? She is a half-wit and a fanatic."

... but doubt lurks behind the mask of her face. </DefaultText>
