      <DefaultText>"Huzzah! The quest thickens!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>254</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her laughter rings throughout the fortress like a death knell. "Oh, she *is* powerful. Of that have no doubt, castoff. And *I* am sure she will not be as helpful to you as you think."

Her smile disappears as quickly as it arrived.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>255</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira's face is red with anger, and you can see the veins throbbing in her forehead. Her voice has lost its cultured edge. "Is it true? You *bonded* with it? I didn't even think you'd succeed, let alone usurp what authority I had left. I should have killed you myself!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>256</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira's gaze is strong and unflinching, though her face is lined, and stress marks her mouth. "Impressive," she says, though her words are clipped. "Even with everything I'd heard you had done, I did not actually think you would succeed."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>260</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I did everything I could to honor our deal."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>261</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You lied to me. *You're* the First."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>262</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I learned the talisman's purpose - to activate the resonance chamber and kill all the castoffs. Why do *you* want it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>263</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Now tell me the truth about the First Castoff."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>264</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Indeed." She narrows her eyes. "Now, for the information I promised you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>265</ID>
      <DefaultText>She frowns. "Very well. There's really no point in *not* telling you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>266</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her laughter scratches harshly against your ears. "Obviously."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>267</ID>
      <DefaultText>She scowls. "The Bloom told you, didn't it? Yes, it's true, for all the good it will do you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>268</ID>
      <DefaultText>She smirks. "An interesting question, one that deserves an answer."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>269</ID>
      <DefaultText>She raises her chin high. Some kind of energy shimmers across her body. "*I* am the First Castoff. I have kept myself hidden for a century and more, watching, waiting, letting our damned sire execute his twisted plans thinking *he* had the upper hand. But we have plans of our own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>270</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As you can see, my agents have retrieved the resonance chamber from the Reef.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>271</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>272</ID>
      <DefaultText>Though it was not without trouble. I had to send a second foray after the first had failed.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>273</ID>
      <DefaultText>With Mazzof returned, we can use the chamber to sever the Tidal connection that draws the Sorrow to us like a war moth. Then we will be free forever - from the Sorrow, from having to hide in Miel Avest or this wretched Bloom, from all of our sire's stratagems. We will finally be ourselves."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>274</ID>
      <DefaultText>You didn't notice while the First was speaking, but Matkina's eyes are staring at one of the First's companions. She actually looks *frightened*. If it's at all possible, she looks paler than normal. "Tash."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>275</ID>
      <DefaultText>She lifts the talisman in her hand, examining its shining surface. "Our freedom is finally at hand, thanks to you." She laughs to herself softly, as though to some inside joke. "I have no doubt you have questions - from what I hear, you *always* have questions. Ask them. Then let's celebrate our freedom together."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>276</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Our freedom is finally at hand, thanks to you." She laughs to herself softly, as though to some inside joke. "I have no doubt you have questions - from what I hear, you *always* have questions. You may ask them while Mazzof finishes his work."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>277</ID>
      <DefaultText>Now that she says his name, it's obvious. This is the man whose body you inhabited in Matkina's merecaster so long ago. His only reply is a leering grin.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>278</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>279</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We need to talk about the chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>280</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I want to talk about the chamber again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>281</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>282</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How long have you been hiding here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>283</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why didn't you just tell me you were the First from the beginning?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>284</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We should use the chamber to weaken the Sorrow. We might be able to kill it!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>285</ID>
      <DefaultText>"*I* want to activate the chamber, merging all castoff consciousnesses into myself."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>286</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have no more questions. Activate the chamber and stop the Sorrow."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>287</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's not worth killing each other over. Here's the talisman. Do what you will."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>288</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>289</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your plan will kill the castoffs. I won't let that happen."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>290</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've decided. I can't let you kill us all, no matter what."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>291</ID>
      <DefaultText>She laughs. "Perhaps you should've thought of that *before* you gave me the talisman. I'll kill you before I let you get near that chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>292</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her voice cuts with a sharp edge. "Are you a fool? The Sorrow *cannot* be killed. You, however, can... which you'll discover if you try to get anywhere near that chamber. The only reason you're alive at all is because I'm optimistic - I hope you're smarter than that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>293</ID>
      <DefaultText>She nods. "It would be foolish to do anything else. Come, brothers and sisters. Our freedom awaits!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>294</ID>
      <DefaultText>She bristles. "You think just because I no longer control the Bloom that you can defeat us all? Try it. I was always going to have to kill you anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>295</ID>
      <DefaultText>She shrugs. "Try and stop me. I was always going to have to kill you anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>296</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then you are a fool."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>297</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait. Let me think about it first."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>298</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Go ahead and try."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>299</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's nothing to think about, fool! In a matter of moments, Mazzof will have the chamber activated and it will be over. But fine." She waves a hand dismissively. "*Think*."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>300</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Keep him away from the chamber! Paint the walls with his blood!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"Keep her away from the chamber! Paint the walls with her blood!"</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>301</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why would you have to kill me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>302</ID>
      <DefaultText>She sets her shoulders strong. "You are *his* key - the catalyst he created to activate the chamber. He would use it to subsume all of us into himself - to *kill* us, do you understand? I have been trying to stop that from happening ever since I learned what our sire's true plans *were*. Then when you spoke to Mazzof in Ossiphagan - using poor Zerian's body - I knew he was close. I knew where you would appear, but not when. I've been watching Miel Avest ever since, waiting for you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>303</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's all I wanted to know. Let's activate the chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>304</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>305</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This isn't right. Give me the talisman back."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>306</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I *won't* let you activate that chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>307</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've decided. I can't let you activate the chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>308</ID>
      <DefaultText>She clutches her belly and laughs, long and hard. The other castoffs surrounding you join her. It's several moments before she calms enough to say, "I can't believe you're serious. Maybe next time you won't be so quick to hand over your only bargaining chip."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>309</ID>
      <DefaultText>She bristles. "You are no longer amusing. You think just because you bonded with the Bloom that you can defeat us all? Go ahead and try. I was always going to have to kill you anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>310</ID>
      <DefaultText>She shrugs. "Go ahead and try. I was always going to have to kill you anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>311</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait. Let me think about it first."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>312</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's nothing to think about, fool! I already have he talisman. But fine." She waves a hand dismissively. "*Think*."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>313</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Go ahead and try."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>314</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Keep him away from the chamber!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"Keep her away from the chamber!"</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>315</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of *course* we do." Her tone is patronizing. "Very well. What do you want to know? What can't your curiosity live without?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>316</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What about it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>317</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>318</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I thought *my* body was the catalyst to the chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>319</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can my body still activate the chamber then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>320</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me again, *can* my body still activate the chamber?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>321</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>322</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It is. The Changing God created your body specifically to activate the chamber, to channel its powers. We discovered you had become a castoff when you spoke to Mazzof through Zerian Daywalker. Your body was designed to control the Tidal connection between us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>323</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course it can. Mazzof has repaired the machine, not broken it further." Her voice gains a sharp edge to it. "But rest assured, if you go anywhere *near* that chamber, I will kill you myself."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>324</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes. But I'll kill you if you try."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>325</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've learned that in activating the chamber, it can be used to weaken the Sorrow. Is that true?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>326</ID>
      <DefaultText>She looks to Mazzof. You can't read the man's expression, but the First says, "Perhaps. But what would that accomplish? The Sorrow has been 'weakened' many times, yet it does not die. I will not risk our lives like that. Severing the Tidal connections between us is our only hope of stopping the Sorrow and surviving."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>327</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your plan will kill the castoffs, not free them. We *need* the connection in order to live."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>328</ID>
      <DefaultText>She scoffs. "What ridiculous conjecture. Where did you hear that?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>329</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A memory of our sire, when I found Mazzof."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>330</ID>
      <DefaultText>(Lie) "The Changing God told me himself."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>331</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's none of your business where I heard it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>332</ID>
      <DefaultText>She stares at you for several moments. Then finally she says, "No, it's impossible."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>333</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ha! He lies. Have you not learned this yet? He will say anything to accomplish his goals."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>334</ID>
      <DefaultText>She sniffs. "It's irrelevant since it's utter nonsense."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>335</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Sorrow tracks us with the Tides. In severing the Tidal connection between us - the Labyrinth, our sire called it - we will no longer be connected to the Tides. We will no longer abuse them, and the Sorrow will stop its hunt. We will be free. It *must* be done."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>336</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>337</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Is there any other way to stop the Sorrow?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>338</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me again, is there any other way to stop the Sorrow?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>339</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>340</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There is one other way." She chuckles darkly. "Our sire's way - suck every living castoff back into a single body. But what good is that? No. The only way to stop the Sorrow is to remove what it seeks. It hunts us because our bodies abuse the Tides. In severing the connection, that abuse will end."

She scoffs. "Our sire didn't know what he was doing when he made our bodies. The Sorrow is the consequence. But I will undo his mistakes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>341</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There is not. Our bodies must stop abusing the Tides - either by severing our Tidal connection or by absorbing us into a single body and mind."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>342</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I want to ask you about something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>343</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>344</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course you do. We are safe here, but don't tarry more than you must. I can *taste* our freedom."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>345</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course you do. Ask them now, before Mazzof has completed the chamber's activation."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>346</ID>
      <DefaultText>She shrugs. "A decade? More? I rescued Mazzof from the ghibra after our sire abandoned him. The Bloom's hatred of the Sorrow, and its power to keep it at bay, was known to me, so we came here in disguise."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>347</ID>
      <DefaultText>She crosses her arms. "Frankly? I don't trust you. There are certain... *voices* in your head. I can't know what side you're *really* on, so it was safer to use you instead."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>348</ID>
      <DefaultText>"*You* destroyed Miel Avest. You slaughtered all those castoffs!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>349</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Did *I* slaughter them, or was it their own cowardice? Holed up beneath those shields like frightened laaks."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>350</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Voices in my head? What are you talking about?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>351</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I can't tell if you're being coy or stupid." She stares at you a moment. "I've known the Changing God was in your mind since you spoke to Mazzof in Ossiphagan. I was there. *I* am the Chimaera. With the Changing God alive, all my plans, and all of our lives, were in jeopardy. Rest assured, I will do *anything* to stop him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>352</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You'd do *anything* to stop our sire? Even kill me and countless innocents?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>353</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What is your plan for the resonance chamber?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>354</ID>
      <DefaultText>She smirks. "That wasn't part of our deal. But seeing as I was going to tell you anyway, I suppose I shouldn't be stingy. You, after all, have as much of a stake in this as I do."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>355</ID>
      <DefaultText>She narrows her eyes. "You are as helpful as I had heard. You should be careful. Not everyone you meet is *worth* helping. Now, for the information I promised you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>356</ID>
      <DefaultText>She frowns. "I'd heard you were a careful man. Very well. There's no point in keeping it from you longer."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>She frowns. "I'd heard you were a careful woman. Very well. There's no point in keeping it from you longer."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>357</ID>
      <DefaultText>Suddenly, several familiar castoffs materialize out of nowhere. You can't place all of their faces, but you immediately recognize Paj Rekken.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>358</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're dead. I... I killed you." Her brow furrows. "Didn't I?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>359</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's certainly what you *remember*." His unpleasant grin widens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>360</ID>
      <DefaultText>She cocks her head to the side. "How do you...? You are more clever than my information suggests. Though perhaps not, if you have not yet divined *why* I would have to kill you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>361</ID>
      <DefaultText>She crosses her arms. "When you escaped the sanctuary, I panicked. Years of planning undone! But then you came here, to me. The trip to the Heart was a fool's errand, you know. Whether you succeeded or not, I would have what I need - either you'd be dead, and our sire's plans with you, or else I'd have Mazzof back to enact my own plans... and our sire's plans would no longer matter."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>362</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>363</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I had no choice. With the chamber out of my control, you were too dangerous to let live. Do you understand? He doesn't think of us as individuals, as people. He would have snuffed us *all* without a second thought! Even now, I find myself wondering whether I should annihilate you, just to be on the safe side." She takes a deep breath. "A few casualties for the sake of all of us? That is worth the risk to me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>364</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her voice sounds like it's cracking slightly.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>365</ID>
      <DefaultText>She shakes her head. "If they had any courage, any care for the plight of their siblings, they would be out *there* fighting against our sire. I would have found them, taken them into my fold as I took in so many." Her voice trails off.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>366</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her voice lowers. "But of course our sire doesn't want to *sever* that connection. He wants to *use* it to draw all castoffs back into himself, snuffing us out." She lowers her chin menacingly. "I *won't* let that happen, so Mazzof has reconfigured the chamber to work with any castoff."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>367</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Our sire learned it from a ghibra castoff named Thom. Thom said both our sire's plans and yours would kill us all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>368</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thom..." She stares at you for several moments. Then finally she says, "No. Thom is mistaken. What could he know about the details of my plan?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>369</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But you *betrayed* the old Memovira. Why take over if you only came here to hide?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>370</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He was weak, and I needed his resources. I had to find the resonance chamber before our sire could activate it." She chuckles. "Controlling the power of the Bloom was a nice bonus."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>371</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When the Bloom began turning against the old Memovira, I saw an opportunity. I needed his resources to find the resonance chamber before our sire found a way to activate it." She chuckles. "Now the Bloom has turned against me, but it won't matter soon."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>372</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How was Mazzof taken from you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>373</ID>
      <DefaultText>She sighs, frustrated, but not at you. "When I rescued Mazzof from the ghibra, we did what our sire could not, liberating the talisman from their Menagerie. I kept it with me, in the fortress, for many years. It was safe... or so I thought."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>374</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her voice grows hard. "The Bloom turned on me without warning, or perhaps there were signs I missed. It devoured a large chunk of the fortress... and Mazzof's workshop with it. I have endeavored to keep it out ever since, but it was too late. Mazzof was gone. He's lucky it was *me* the Bloom wanted, else he would have been devoured immediately."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>375</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>376</ID>
      <DefaultText>The trim figure of Bericael is also among them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>377</ID>
      <DefaultText>

"Our sire thought to use the resonance chamber to subsume us, but I have learned it can stop the Sorrow in another way. It is the door to our freedom, and you have returned to me my key."

Then the Memovira - the *First* - makes a sweeping gesture toward Mazzof behind her.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>379</ID>
      <DefaultText>Script Node 379</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>380</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This way. Draw any weapons and you'll die in short order."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>381</ID>
      <DefaultText>Script Node 381</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>382</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So, the hero returns."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"So, the heroine returns."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>383</ID>
      <DefaultText>[The Memovira comments on the castoffs that just teleported into the room, then sweeps her hand to reveal the door opening behind her.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>384</ID>
      <DefaultText>She addresses her guards. "See that the castoff doesn't get lost on his way out."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>She addresses her guards. "See that the castoff doesn't get lost on her way out."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>385</ID>
      <DefaultText>Script Node 385</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>386</ID>
      <DefaultText>Script Node 386</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>387</ID>
      <DefaultText>She stares at the Memovira... the First. "What's in your mind? It must squirm like maggots. How do you justify yourself?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>388</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why did you send me if you thought I wouldn't succeed?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>389</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her voice cuts with a sharp edge. "Did you think I brought these castoffs out here to boast? We'll kill you before you get near that chamber. The only reason I haven't yet is because I'm optimistic - I hope you're smarter than that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>390</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't think I didn't consider it. Your mere existence is a danger to all our kind." She smirks. "Yes, castoff, *our* kind."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>391</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Our freedom is finally at hand." She turns her face away from you as though you no longer mattered. "As soon as Mazzof finishes his work, your betrayal will be a pointless footnote."

She sighs. "I can feel your childish curiosity from here. Ask your questions then. But don't expect any charity."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>392</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When the Bloom began turning against the old Memovira, I saw an opportunity. I needed his resources to find the resonance chamber before our sire found a way to activate it."

She utters a low growl. "Now with your betrayal, the Bloom has turned on me as well - but it won't matter soon."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>393</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What you did down there was... unexpected." She looks you up and down, then mutters, "I can't imagine why it would choose *you*. You must have depths not immediately apparent."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>394</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your actions in the Bloom's heart have justified my distrust... and shown that I trusted you too much even so."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>395</ID>
      <DefaultText>She turns to you, and you can hear a tinge of dark humor in her voice. "Your time will come as well, you know. The Bloom can't be trusted any more than you can."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>396</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira's face is red with anger, and you can see the veins throbbing in her forehead. Her voice has lost its cultured edge. "Is it true? You allowed *her* to bond with it? So you are both traitors! I should have killed her - killed *both* of you - when you gave me the opportunity."

Her lip quivers with rage. "Rest assured, my memory is long and patient. If you survive this day, know that your betrayal survives with you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>397</ID>
      <DefaultText>"*If* we survive this day? The Bloom is at my back now, usurper, and together we will take revenge for what you did to your predecessor - to my *friends*!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>398</ID>
      <DefaultText>An odd smirk emerges on her face. "Surely that's not all you want revenge for, 'Kina. You and I have more history that *that*."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>399</ID>
      <DefaultText>You didn't notice while the First was speaking, but Matkina is staring at one of the First's companions. "Tash."

Now that she says his name, it's obvious. This is the man whose body you inhabited in the merecaster so long ago. Matkina's expression becomes quizzical, as though a scar had appeared on her arm and she couldn't remember how it got there. "You're dead. I killed you... didn't I?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>400</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Interesting." She frowns. "I'll make sure to finish the job then. The Bloom will help me with that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>401</ID>
      <DefaultText>His leering grin disappears in a flash.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>